                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.667,
                                "byte_start": 106496,
                                "byte_stop": 141187,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has our opinion in case 10-507, Pacific Operators Offshore versus Valladolid."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.667,
                        "stop": 250.775,
                        "byte_start": 141187,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15100,
                            "name": "Clarence Thomas",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/clarence_thomas",
                            "last_name": "Thomas",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2744,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 688194000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2744"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32680,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49064,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/clarence_thomas.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8870,
                            "identifier": "clarence_thomas"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.667,
                                "stop": 15.457,
                                "byte_start": 141187,
                                "byte_stop": 168354,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on a writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.457,
                                "stop": 36.323,
                                "byte_start": 168354,
                                "byte_stop": 251841,
                                "text": "Petitioner operates two oil platforms on the Outer Continental Shelf off the coast of California, one by Valladolid, one of petitioner\u0027s employees spent most of his time working on one of these offshore platforms, but he was killed in an accident while working at petitioner\u0027s onshore facility."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 36.323,
                                "stop": 47.038,
                                "byte_start": 251841,
                                "byte_stop": 294682,
                                "text": "Valladolid\u0027s widow, the respondent here, sought workers\u0027 compensation benefits pursuant to the Outer Continental Shelf Lands Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.038,
                                "stop": 67.866,
                                "byte_start": 294682,
                                "byte_stop": 378065,
                                "text": "The Lands Act extends the workers\u0027 compensation coverage provided by another statute, the Longshore and Harbor Workers\u0027 Compensation Act to injuries occurring as a result of operations conducted on the Shelf for the purpose of extracting natural resources."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.866,
                                "stop": 82.871,
                                "byte_start": 378065,
                                "byte_stop": 438042,
                                "text": "An administrative law judge dismissed the respondent\u0027s claim reasoning that the Lands Act did not cover Valladolid\u0027s fatal injury because his accident occurred on land rather than on the Shelf."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.871,
                                "stop": 87.046,
                                "byte_start": 438042,
                                "byte_stop": 454760,
                                "text": "The Labor Department\u0027s Benefit Review Board affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 87.046,
                                "stop": 106.641,
                                "byte_start": 454760,
                                "byte_stop": 533128,
                                "text": "The Ninth Circuit reversed, concluding that the Lands Act did not incorporate a strict geographic restriction, but rather required a substantial nexus between a worker\u0027s injury and his employer\u0027s extractive operations on the Shelf."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.641,
                                "stop": 111.125,
                                "byte_start": 533128,
                                "byte_stop": 551100,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the clerk today, we affirm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 111.125,
                                "stop": 123.131,
                                "byte_start": 551100,
                                "byte_stop": 599061,
                                "text": "We reject the petitioner\u0027s argument that the Lands Act extends Longshore Act coverage only to employees whose injuries occur on the Shelf."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 123.131,
                                "stop": 128.672,
                                "byte_start": 599061,
                                "byte_stop": 621213,
                                "text": "Nothing in the text of the Lands Act supports such a restriction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.672,
                                "stop": 145.005,
                                "byte_start": 621213,
                                "byte_stop": 686519,
                                "text": "The statute has only two requirements, the employer\u0027s extractive operations must be conducted on the Shelf and the employee\u0027s injury must occur as a result of those operations."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 145.005,
                                "stop": 165.93,
                                "byte_start": 686519,
                                "byte_stop": 770320,
                                "text": "Had Congress intended to limit the scope of Lands Act coverage solely to injuries that occur on the Shelf then Congress could have easily done so as demonstrated by the explicit geographic restrictions that appear in other subsections of the Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 165.93,
                                "stop": 180.948,
                                "byte_start": 770320,
                                "byte_stop": 830297,
                                "text": "We are also unpersuaded by petitioner\u0027s alternative argument which requires a nonintuitive reading of the Lands Act in light of other unrelated provisions in the Longshore Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.948,
                                "stop": 194.78,
                                "byte_start": 830297,
                                "byte_stop": 885676,
                                "text": "We find it unlikely that Congress intended to restrict the scope of -- of the Lands Act Workers\u0027 Compensation scheme through the convoluted combination of two separate legislative Acts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 194.78,
                                "stop": 201.666,
                                "byte_start": 885676,
                                "byte_stop": 913262,
                                "text": "Instead, we conclude that the substantial nexus test faithfully interprets the text of the Lands Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 201.666,
                                "stop": 220.584,
                                "byte_start": 913262,
                                "byte_stop": 988912,
                                "text": "We understand that test to require an injured employee to establish a significant causal link between his injury and his employer\u0027s extractive operations on the Shelf in order to be eligible for workers\u0027 compensation benefits under the Lands Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 220.584,
                                "stop": 229.785,
                                "byte_start": 988912,
                                "byte_stop": 1025693,
                                "text": "Whether an injured employee qualifies for Lands Act coverage will depend on the specific circumstances of his case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 229.785,
                                "stop": 242.069,
                                "byte_start": 1025693,
                                "byte_stop": 1074803,
                                "text": "It was thus proper for the Ninth Circuit to remand this case for the Benefits Review Board to apply the substantial nexus test to the circumstances presented in this case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 242.069,
                                "stop": 250.775,
                                "byte_start": 1074803,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed an opinion concurring in part and concurring in the judgment in which Justice Alito joins."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
